        Get one more independent bid &rarr;
      </a>
    </div>

    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Good luck with the decision.</p>

    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
    <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;color:#71717a;font-style:italic;">
      P.S. Once you've signed: keep every email, certificate, model number, and AHRI number from the install. If your install is a heat pump, ask the contractor for the manufacturer's certification statement &mdash; you'll need it to claim the IRA Section 25C federal tax credit (worth up to $2,000 against your federal taxes). And for any warranty claim down the line, the paperwork is what makes the difference between &ldquo;covered&rdquo; and &ldquo;good luck.&rdquo;
    </p>

